The '''Fremennik Isles''' are a volcanic archipelago in the [[Lunar Sea]] consisting of six islands: [[Jatizso]], [[Neitiznot]], an uninhabited island containing the [[Central Fremennik Isles mine]], an island containing the [[Ice Troll Caves]], an island north of Neitiznot where [[honour guard]]s fight [[ice troll]]s and an island north of Jatizso where [[Guard (Jatizso)|guards]] also fight ice trolls. Although the islands of [[Miscellania]] and [[Etceteria]] are also inhabited by Fremennik, they are not part of the Fremennik Isles.

They are the location where most of the [[The Fremennik Isles]] quest takes place. Points of interest include the towns of Neitiznot and Jatizso, [[Jatizso mine]], the [[Central Fremennik Isles mine]] and the [[yak]] enclosure. The ice trolls north of Jatizso are commonly killed on [[Slayer task/Trolls|slayer task]] due to their valuable drops and the island being [[multicombat]].

The [[East Fremennik Isles mine]] and the [[West Fremennik Isles mine]] are also located on the isles.

==Location==
The Fremennik Isles are located north-west of [[Rellekka]]. There are several ways to get there:

*After completing the Elite [[Fremennik Diary]], use an [[Enchanted lyre|Enchanted Lyre]]
*Use the Enchanted Lyre to get to [[Rellekka]], and talk to [[Maria Gunnars]] or [[Mord Gunnars]] on the northernmost dock. There is no cost for this travel.

==History==
The location of the Fremennik Isles was uncharted{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Jatizso ventured far into uncharted oceans, [...]}} until they were settled by the two youngest sons of a Fremennik king who ruled four generations before the present:{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Four generations ago there was a mighty king who ruled wisely and was loved by all. He had many sons, [...]. His youngest two sons, however, were a problem.}} Jatizso and Neitiznot.{{CiteNPC|npc=Maria Gunnars|quote=Their names were Jatizso and Neitiznot.}} As punishment for their squabbling, the king banished them from the realm until they had conquered lands of their own.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=As punishment for their squabbling he banished his sons from his realm, ordering that neither should return until they had conquered lands of their own.}} Jatizso came across a land rich in minerals, deep fjords and sweeping mountains.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=At last a promising land was sighted, a land rich in minerals, deep fjords and sweeping mountains.}} He then claimed the land, named it after himself,{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Jatizso claimed the land and named it after himself.}} built a citadel and set out to explore the kingdom.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=A mighty citadel was constructed to protect his land; then Jatizso set forth to explore his new kingdom.}}

Jatizso discovered a green and fertile island{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Crossing a few fjords, Jatizso spied an island which remained green and fertile, even at such latitude.}} only to find that his brother had already founded his own settlement on it.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Jatizso was horrified when his brother appeared on the battlements and cried 'This is my land! Go find yer own'.}} The blood feud between the followers of Jatizso and the followers of Neitiznot has persisted to the present day.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=And so the blood feud continued.}}

Jatizso is currently ruled by [[King Gjuki Sorvott IV]] and Neitiznot by Burgher [[Mawnis Burowgar]]. Recently, a massive army of [[ice troll]]s seized the northern island.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Quite recently a massive troll army seized one of the islands to the north, while our townships' militias were busy fighting one another.}} While Neitiznot's troops were busy laying siege to Jatizso, the trolls marched down and razed Neitiznot to the ground.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=They marched down and razed Neitiznot to the ground while Neitiznot's troops laid siege to Jatizso.}} Mawnis's wife and youngest son were killed during this raid.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Anyway, the Burgher lost his wife and youngest son in the trolls' raid and has been a changed man since.}}

The rulers have agreed to a peace until the trolls are dealt with.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mord Gunnars|quote=Anyway, a hasty sort of peace has been agreed until the trolls are dealt with.}} During [[The Fremennik Isles]] quest, the player character aids the warriors of Neitiznot in defeating the [[Ice Troll King]].

